## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="180fd-102">La classe <xref:System.Runtime.Caching.MemoryCache> è un'implementazione concreta della classe astratta <xref:System.Runtime.Caching.ObjectCache> .</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="180fd-102">The <xref:System.Runtime.Caching.MemoryCache> class is a concrete implementation of the abstract <xref:System.Runtime.Caching.ObjectCache> class.</span></span>  
  
> [!NOTE]
>  <span data-ttu-id="180fd-103">Il <xref:System.Runtime.Caching.MemoryCache> classe è simile a ASP.NET <xref:System.Web.Caching.Cache> classe.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="180fd-103">The <xref:System.Runtime.Caching.MemoryCache> class is similar to the ASP.NET <xref:System.Web.Caching.Cache> class.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="180fd-104">Il <xref:System.Runtime.Caching.MemoryCache> classe dispone di molte proprietà e metodi per l'accesso della cache che risulterà familiare all'utente se si usa ASP.NET <xref:System.Web.Caching.Cache> classe.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="180fd-104">The <xref:System.Runtime.Caching.MemoryCache> class has many properties and methods for accessing the cache that will be familiar to you if you have used the ASP.NET <xref:System.Web.Caching.Cache> class.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="180fd-105">Le principali differenze tra il <xref:System.Web.Caching.Cache> e <xref:System.Runtime.Caching.MemoryCache> classi sono che le <xref:System.Runtime.Caching.MemoryCache> classe è stata modificata per renderlo utilizzabile da [!INCLUDE[dnprdnshort](~/includes/dnprdnshort-md.md)] le applicazioni che non sono le applicazioni ASP.NET.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="180fd-105">The main differences between the <xref:System.Web.Caching.Cache> and <xref:System.Runtime.Caching.MemoryCache> classes are that the <xref:System.Runtime.Caching.MemoryCache> class has been changed to make it usable by [!INCLUDE[dnprdnshort](~/includes/dnprdnshort-md.md)] applications that are not ASP.NET applications.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="180fd-106">Ad esempio, il <xref:System.Runtime.Caching.MemoryCache> classe non ha dipendenze dal `System.Web` assembly.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="180fd-106">For example, the <xref:System.Runtime.Caching.MemoryCache> class has no dependencies on the `System.Web` assembly.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="180fd-107">Un'altra differenza è che è possibile creare più istanze del <xref:System.Runtime.Caching.MemoryCache> classe per l'uso nella stessa applicazione e nella stessa <xref:System.AppDomain> istanza.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="180fd-107">Another difference is that you can create multiple instances of the <xref:System.Runtime.Caching.MemoryCache> class for use in the same application and in the same <xref:System.AppDomain> instance.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="180fd-108">Il <xref:System.Runtime.Caching.MemoryCache> classe nepovoluje hodnotu `null` come valore nella cache.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="180fd-108">The <xref:System.Runtime.Caching.MemoryCache> class does not allow `null` as a value in the cache.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="180fd-109">Qualsiasi tentativo di aggiungere o modificare una voce della cache con il valore `null` avrà esito negativo.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="180fd-109">Any attempt to add or change a cache entry with a value of `null` will fail.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="180fd-110">Il <xref:System.Runtime.Caching.MemoryCache> il tipo non implementa *memorizza nella cache aree*.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="180fd-110">The <xref:System.Runtime.Caching.MemoryCache> type does not implement *cache regions*.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="180fd-111">Pertanto, quando si chiama <xref:System.Runtime.Caching.MemoryCache> metodi che implementano i metodi di base che contengono un parametro per le aree, non passare un valore per il parametro.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="180fd-111">Therefore, when you call <xref:System.Runtime.Caching.MemoryCache> methods that implement base methods that contain a parameter for regions, do not pass a value for the parameter.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="180fd-112">I metodi che usano il parametro regione tutte forniscono un valore predefinito `null` valore.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="180fd-112">The methods that use the region parameter all supply a default `null` value.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="180fd-113">Ad esempio, il <xref:System.Runtime.Caching.MemoryCache.AddOrGetExisting%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> overload del metodo ha un `regionName` parametro il cui valore predefinito è `null`.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="180fd-113">For example, the <xref:System.Runtime.Caching.MemoryCache.AddOrGetExisting%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> method overload has a `regionName` parameter whose default value is `null`.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="180fd-114">L'esempio seguente dichiara un riferimento all'istanza predefinita della cache di memoria.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="180fd-114">The following example declares a reference to the default memory cache instance.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="180fd-115">La voce della cache Usa un <xref:System.Runtime.Caching.CacheItemPolicy> oggetto da fornire i dettagli di scadenza e rimozione per la voce della cache.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="180fd-115">The cache entry uses a <xref:System.Runtime.Caching.CacheItemPolicy> object to provide eviction and expiration details for the cache entry.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="180fd-116">Usa anche un <xref:System.Runtime.Caching.ChangeMonitor> oggetto per monitorare lo stato dei dati di origine, ovvero un file, nel file system.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="180fd-116">It also uses a <xref:System.Runtime.Caching.ChangeMonitor> object to monitor the state of the source data (which is a file) on the file system.</span></span>  
  
```vb  
Private Sub btnGet_Click(ByVal sender As Object, ByVal e As EventArgs)   
    Dim cache As ObjectCache = MemoryCache.[Default]   
    Dim fileContents As String = TryCast(cache("filecontents"), String)   
  
    If fileContents Is Nothing Then   
        Dim policy As New CacheItemPolicy()   
        Dim filePaths As New List(Of String)()   
        filePaths.Add("c:\cache\example.txt")   
  
        policy.ChangeMonitors.Add(New HostFileChangeMonitor(filePaths))   
  
        ' Fetch the file contents.  
        fileContents = File.ReadAllText("c:\cache\example.txt")   
  
        cache.[Set]("filecontents", fileContents, policy)   
    End If   
  
    Label1.Text = fileContents  
End Sub  
```  
  
```csharp  
private void btnGet_Click(object sender, EventArgs e)  
{  
    ObjectCache cache = MemoryCache.Default;  
    string fileContents = cache["filecontents"] as string;  
  
    if (fileContents == null)  
    {  
        CacheItemPolicy policy = new CacheItemPolicy();  
  
        List<string> filePaths = new List<string>();  
        filePaths.Add("c:\\cache\\example.txt");  
  
        policy.ChangeMonitors.Add(new   
        HostFileChangeMonitor(filePaths));  
  
        // Fetch the file contents.  
        fileContents =   
            File.ReadAllText("c:\\cache\\example.txt");  
  
        cache.Set("filecontents", fileContents, policy);  
    }  
  
    Label1.Text = fileContents;  
}  
```
